<p>{{ site.name }} is a full-service shop — we don't just manufacture, we install, repair, store, and maintain everything we create. We're craftsmen at our trade and build long-lasting canvas solutions for residential, commercial, and marine customers. Our products outlast our competitors, but we also offer additional services so our customers get the most out of their canvas investment. Below are a few of the services we provide — we're happy to go into more detail about any of them, or custom-create a service plan that meets your needs. Give us a call at <a href="tel:{{ site.contact.phone_e164 }}">{{ site.contact.phone }}</a> and we'll be happy to work with you.</p>

<h2 id="marine-canvas-repairs">Marine Canvas Repairs</h2>

<p>Canvas repairs done correctly will help keep your boat in good condition.</p>

<p>We can repair most any problem, from stitches coming apart to the long tear in the cover. Many bimini tops, convertible tops, and enclosures can be repaired. Is the frame bent or broken? A new frame for your top can be ordered, fabricated, or we can repair the old one.</p>

<p>Is your existing marine canvas in need of repair? We can fix most problems — stitches coming apart, window and zipper replacement, and those nasty unexpected tears. Remember, many bimini tops, convertible tops, and enclosures can be repaired. Trust us to fix your marine canvas at a fraction of the cost of new.</p>

<h2 id="marine-awning-repairs">Canvas Awning Repairs</h2>

<p>We specialize in bringing life back to older awnings. Need to extend the life of an existing canvas awning? Need to fix a tear, repair a bent or broken frame? Or perhaps you'd like to alter the existing frame for an entirely new look? {{ site.name }} will work with you to bring your ideas into reality.</p>

<h2 id="canvas-awning-services">Canvas Awning Service</h2>

<p>Protect your investment by signing up for our offsite canvas awning service. At the end of the season, we come out and winterize your awning — removing the canvas, sealing the frame, and transporting your awning to our shop. We inspect your awning, clean it, and make routine repairs to return your canvas awning as close as possible to its original state. We can also make any alterations you require. We then store your awning in our facility until the next season arrives, and work with you to schedule a time to return and install it for the new season. Don't risk winter damage (mice and rodent damage, car runovers — we've seen it all) — leave the storage and monitoring to us.</p>

